S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Steep Coast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A coast backed by rock or earth cliffs, gives a good radar return and is useful for visual identification from a considerable distance off, where cliffs alternate with low lying coast along the shoreline.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flat Coast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A level coast with no obvious topographic features.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mangrove
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: One of several genera of tropical trees or shrubs which produce many prop roots and grow along low-lying coasts into shallow water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Marshy Shore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A shoreline area made up of spongy land saturated with water. It may have a shallow covering of water, usually with a considerable amount of vegetation appearing above the surface.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Coast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical cliff forming the seaward edge of an ice shelf, ranging in height from 2 metres to 50 metres or more above sea level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Kilometres Per Hour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit of speed, expressing the number of kilometres travelled in one hour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Miles Per Hour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An imperial and United States customary unit of speed expressing the number of statute miles covered in one hour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Knots
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A nautical unit of speed. One knot is one nautical mile per hour. The name is derived from the knots in the log line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Installation Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of fixed installation buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Catenary Anchor Leg Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Incorporates a large buoy which remains on the surface at all times and is moored by 4 or more anchors. Mooring hawsers and cargo hoses lead from a turntable on top of the buoy, so that the buoy does not turn as the ship swings to wind and stream.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Single Buoy Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large mooring buoy used by tankers to load and unload in port approaches or in offshore oil and gas fields.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nature Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tract of land or water managed so as to preserve its flora, fauna, physical features, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bird Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where birds are bred and protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Game Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where wild animals or birds hunted for sport or food are kept undisturbed for private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seal Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where seals are protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Historic Wreck Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area around certain wrecks of historical importance to protect the wrecks from unauthorized interference by diving, salvage or deposition (including anchoring).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Research Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area where marine research takes place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fish Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where fish (including shellfish and crustaceans) are protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ecological Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tract of land or water managed so as to preserve the relation of plants and living creatures to each other and to their surroundings.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Environmentally Sensitive Sea Area (ESSA)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 27:Environmentally Sensitive Sea Area (ESSA) (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Particularly Sensitive Sea Area (PSSA)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 28:Particularly Sensitive Sea Area (PSSA) (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coral Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where coral is protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recreation Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which recreational activities regularly take place and therefore vessel movement may be restricted.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Group
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of signals, the combination of signals or the morse character(s) within one period of full sequence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vessel Class
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The classification of a vessel, normally as defined by length or gross tonnage.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Multiplicity Known
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-located group is or is not known.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum scale at which the feature may be used for example for ECDIS presentation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Quality of Horizontal Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The degree of reliability attributed to a position.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A position that is considered to be less than third-order accuracy, but is generally considered to be within 30.5 metres of its correct geographic location. Also may apply to a feature whose position does not remain fixed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Position Doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Of uncertain position. The expression is used principally on charts to indicate that a wreck, shoal, etc., has been reported in various positions and not definitely determined in any.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Jurisdiction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The jurisdiction applicable to an administrative area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Involving more than one country; covering more than one national area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: National
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area administered or controlled by a single nation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: National Sub-Division
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 3:National Sub-Division (missing definition)

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of Surface
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The general material which the land surface or the seabed is composed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mud
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Soft, wet earth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of less than 0.002mm); stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Silt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An unconsolidated sediment whose particles range in size from 0.0039 to 0.0625 millimetres in diameter (between clay and sand size).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A general term for rock and rock fragments ranging in size from pebbles and gravel to boulders or large rock masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Gravel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of 2.0 - 4.0mm); small stones with coarse sand.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pebbles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A small stone worn smooth and rounded by the action of water, sand, ice, etc. ranging in diameter between 4 and 64 millimetres.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cobbles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A naturally rounded stone larger than a pebble.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any formation of natural origin that constitutes an integral part of the lithosphere. The natural occurring material that forms firm, hard, and solid masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lava
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fluid or semi-fluid matter flowing from a volcano. The substance that results from the cooling of the molten rock. Part of the ocean bed is composed of lava.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Hard calcareous skeletons of many tribes of marine polyps.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shells
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The hard outside covering of an animal. Part of the ocean bed is composed of numerous shells of marine animals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boulder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rounded rock with diameter of 256 millimetres or larger.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value considered by the Data Producer to be the maximum (largest) scale at which the data is to be displayed before it can be considered to be “grossly overscaled”.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Marks Navigational - System Of
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The system of navigational buoyage a region complies with.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA A
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA A system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA B
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA B system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids do not conform to any defined system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Main European Inland Waterway Marking System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids as required in international, national or regional regulations that contain the same navigational aids as the European Code for Inland Waterways of UNECE, or if there is no regulation for a waterway, navigational aids as recommended in the European Code for Inland Waterways of UNECE

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The luminous range of a light in a homogenous atmosphere in which the meteorological visibility is 10 sea miles.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Comparison Operator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Numerical comparison.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Less Than or Equal To

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equal To

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Cable
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the cable based on the services provided.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Power Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cable that transmits or distributes electrical power.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Transmission Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Multiple un-insulated cables usually supported by steel lattice towers. Such features are generally more prominent than normal power lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mooring Cable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A chain or very strong fibre or wire rope used to anchor or moor vessels or buoys.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ferry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vessel for transporting passengers, vehicles, and/or goods across a stretch of water, especially as a regular service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Junction Cable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cable used for joining components of complex marine structures, for example mooring trots.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telecommunications Cable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cable used for the transmission and reception of modulated communication waves/signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: non-dangerous wreck
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 1:non-dangerous wreck (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dangerous Wreck
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A wreck submerged at such a depth as to be considered dangerous to surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Distributed Remains of Wreck
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A substantively decayed wreck over which it is safe to navigate but which should be avoided for anchoring, taking the ground or ground fishing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wreck showing mast/masts
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 4:wreck showing mast/masts (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wreck Showing Any Portion of Hull or Superstructure
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Wreck of which any portion of the hull or superstructure is visible at the sounding datum indicated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Lateral Mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of lateral marks in the IALA Buoyage System.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: port-hand lateral mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 1:port-hand lateral mark (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Starboard Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage", the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified port-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Port Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage", the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified starboard-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Height
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the vertical distance to the highest point of the feature, measured from a specified vertical datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vessels Characteristics Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of a particular characteristic such as a dimension or tonnage of a vessel.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Linkage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Location (address) for online access using a URL/URI address or similar addressing scheme.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Display Uncertainties
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement defining whether an encoded feature is to have its horizontal position and vertical accuracies displayed or not.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Area Category
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Category of the designated area

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nationality
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier of membership of a particular nation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Permitted Vessel Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum length of a vessel permitted in a channel or dock, at a berth, or at an anchorage or mooring.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Permitted Draught
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum draught of a vessel permitted along a route, in a channel or dock, at a berth, or over a submerged feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Minimum Altitude
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Height (AGL - above ground level) above surface level to the lowest portion of the feature.

S100FC:uom.S100Base:name: foot
S100FC:uom.S100Base:definition: a unit of length equal to 12 inches, 1/6 of a fathom, or 30.480 centimetres

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: missing definition

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Bottom Vertical Safety Separation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A percentage value that can be applied to a charted depth in order to establish the BVSS clearance.

S100FC:uom.S100Base:name: percent
S100FC:uom.S100Base:definition: by a specified amount in or for every hundred

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The condition of an object at a given instant in time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Permanent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Intended to last or function indefinitely.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occasional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Acting on special occasions; happening irregularly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recommended
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Presented as worthy of confidence, acceptance, use, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not in Use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Use has ceased, but the facility still exists intact; disused.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: periodic/intermittent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 5:periodic/intermittent (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reserved
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Set apart for some specific use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temporary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Meant to last only for a time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Administered by an individual or corporation, rather than a State or a public body.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mandatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Compulsory; enforced.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extinguished
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: No longer lit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Illuminated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lit by flood lights, strip lights, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Historic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Famous in history; of historical interest.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Public
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Belonging to, available to, used or shared by, the community as a whole and not restricted to private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synchronized
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Occur at a time, coincide in point of time, be contemporary or simultaneous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Watched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Looked at or observed over a period of time especially so as to be aware of any movement or change.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unwatched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Usually automatic in operation, without any permanently-stationed personnel to superintend it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Existence Doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A feature that has been reported but has not been definitely determined to exist.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Marked by buoys.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: active/in use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 501:active/in use (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Claimed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A coastal State claims or may claim a specific jurisdiction in accordance with the provisions of International Law.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: practice and/or exercise purposes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 503:practice and/or exercise purposes (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recognised
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: acknowledged and agreed in accordance with the provisions of International Law

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dead
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: not detected by repeated surveys, leading to doubts about the object's existence. (AML)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lifted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an object that has been salvaged or removed. (AML)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mass Grave
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: where a significant number of persons have perished as a direct result of a vessel or structure sinking and their remains cannot be recovered, the wreck and immediate area may be declared as a Mass Grave or more specifically, a War Grave. Such sites are protected from disturbance by International Law. (AML)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Exploration
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a borehole drilled in the search for a new source of oil or gas. (An A-Z of Offshore Oil & Gas by Harry Whitehead, 2nd Ed, 1983, Gulf Publishing Company)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Production
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a borehole that is actively engaged in the extraction of oil or gas from the seabed. (Adapted from An A-Z of Offshore Oil & Gas by Harry Whitehead, 2nd Ed, 1983, Gulf Publishing Company)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Suspended
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a well where the extraction of oil or gas has been temporarily abandoned. When suspended, a well is either plugged (filled with concrete and topped with a steel plate) or capped (well-head equipment is installed over the well). (Adapted from An A-Z of Offshore Oil & Gas by Harry Whitehead, 2nd Ed, 1983, Gulf Publishing Company)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Injection
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a borehole drilled for the purpose of injecting a secondary substance, for example water, into the pore spaces in a reservoir rock to encourage oil or gas to flow into adjacent producing wells. (An A-Z of Offshore Oil & Gas by Harry Whitehead, 2nd Ed, 1983, Gulf Publishing Company)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unspecified
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the status of the object is unspecified.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dormant
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: temporarily quiet, inactive, not being used. (AML).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Proposed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: planned; intended; in accordance with, or achieved by, a careful plan made beforehand (The Concise Oxford Dictionary)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Abandoned
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: completely deserted; given up (adapted from the Concise Oxford Dictionary)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Grey zone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Area of overlap of the unilateral fishing zones of two or more countries

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Indeterminate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area of the sea of indeterminate jurisdiction where no agreed boundary exist.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Multilateral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Involving two or more states as parties to an agreement.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Species
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A group of individuals having common characteristics, specialised from others of the same genus

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Optimum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The largest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Speed Maximum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Rate of motion. The terms speed and velocity are often used interchangeably, but speed is a scalar, having magnitude only, while velocity is a vector quantity, having both magnitude and direction. Speed maximum is the maximum rate of travel that can occur.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Agency Responsible for Production
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifies the agency which produced the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Cardinal Mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The four quadrants (north, east, south and west) are bounded by the true bearings NW-NE, NE-SE, SE-SW and SW-NW taken from the point of interest. A cardinal mark is named after the quadrant in which it is placed. The name of the cardinal mark indicates that it should be passed to the named side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: North Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing NW-NE taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the north side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: East Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing NE-SE taken from the point of interest. It should be passed to the east side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: South Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing SE-SW taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the south side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: West Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing SW-NW taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the west side of the mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Airport/Airfield
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of airport/airfield based on the primary aircraft and user group.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Military Aeroplane Airport
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large military airfield usually equipped with a control tower, hangars and accommodation for the receiving and discharging of passengers or cargo.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Civil Aeroplane Airport
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large airfield usually equipped with a control tower, hangars and accommodation for the receiving and discharging of passengers or cargo.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Military Heliport
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A landing place for helicopters controlled by the military.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Civil Heliport
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A landing place for helicopters, often the roof of a building.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glider Airfield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area of land set aside for the take-off and landing of gliders.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Small Planes Airfield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area of land set aside for the take-off and landing of small aeroplanes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Emergency Airfield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area of land set aside for the take-off and landing of aeroplanes or helicopters in times of emergency.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: search and rescue
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 9:search and rescue (missing definition)

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Operator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of the company operating the installation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Technique of Vertical Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Survey method used to obtain depth information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Echo Sounder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using an instrument that determines depth of water by measuring the time interval between emission of a sonic or ultrasonic signal and return of its echo from the bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Side Scan Sonar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was computed from a record produced by active sonar in which fixed acoustic beams are directed into the water perpendicularly to the direction of travel to scan the seabed and generate a record of the seabed configuration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Multi Beam
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using a wide swath echo sounder that uses multiple beams to measure depths directly below and transverse to the ship's track.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Diver
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by a person skilled in the practice of diving.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Lead Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using a line, graduated with attached marks and fastened to a sounding lead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Vertical Acoustic System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area has been swept using a system comprised of multiple echo sounder transducers attached to booms deployed from the survey vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Electromagnetic Sensor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using an instrument that compares electromagnetic signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Photogrammetry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The science or art of obtaining reliable measurements from photographs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Satellite Imagery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using instruments placed aboard an artificial satellite.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: found by leveling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 12:found by leveling (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Side Scan Sonar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a side scan sonar.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by LIDAR
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using an instrument that measures distance by emitting timed pulses of laser light and measuring the time between emission and reception of the reflected pulses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synthetic Aperture Radar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar with a synthetic aperture antenna which is composed of a large number of elementary transducing elements. The signals are electronically combined into a resulting signal equivalent to that of a single antenna of a given aperture in a given direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hyperspectral Imagery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used to describe the imagery derived from subdividing the electromagnetic spectrum into very narrow bandwidths. These narrow bandwidths may be combined with or subtracted from each other in various ways to form images useful in precise terrain or target analysis.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mechanically Swept
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a line or object below the surface at the desired depth; or least depth(s) and position(s) within an area was identified using the same technique.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference level used for expressing the vertical measurements of points on the earth's surface. Also called datum level, reference plane, levelling datum, datum for sounding reduction, datum for heights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the surface of the sea at a tide station for all stages of the tide over a 19-year period, usually determined from hourly height readings measured from a fixed predetermined reference level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the high waters of spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Sea Level (MSL).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean high water springs (MHWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Higher High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of higher high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary datum defined by a local harbour authority, from which levels and tidal heights are measured by this authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: international great
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 25:international great (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Water Level

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The official legal status of each kind of restricted area defines the kind of restriction(s), for example the restriction for a 'game reserve' may be 'entering prohibited'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Offshore Safety Zone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The area around an offshore installation within which vessels are prohibited from entering without permission. Special regulations protect installations within a safety zone and vessels of all nationalities are required to respect the zone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nature Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tract of land or water managed so as to preserve its flora, fauna, physical features, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bird Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where birds are bred and protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Game Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where wild animals or birds hunted for sport or food are kept undisturbed for private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seal Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where seals are protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Degaussing Range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area, usually about two cables diameter, within which ships' magnetic fields may be measured; sensing instruments and cables are installed on the seabed in the range and there are cables leading from the range to a control position ashore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Military Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area controlled by the military in which restrictions may apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Historic Wreck Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area around certain wrecks of historical importance to protect the wrecks from unauthorized interference by diving, salvage or deposition (including anchoring).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigational Aid Safety Zone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area around a navigational aid which vessels are prohibited from entering.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Minefield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area laid and maintained with explosive mines for defence or practice purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swimming Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which people may swim and therefore vessel movement may be restricted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Waiting Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area reserved for vessels waiting to enter a harbour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Research Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area where marine research takes place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dredging Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area where dredging is taking place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fish Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where fish (including shellfish and crustaceans) are protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ecological Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tract of land or water managed so as to preserve the relation of plants and living creatures to each other and to their surroundings.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Wake Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which a vessels' speed must be reduced in order to reduce the size of the wake it produces.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swinging Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area where vessels turn.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Environmentally Sensitive Sea Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A generic term which may be used to describe a wide range of areas, considered sensitive for a variety of environmental reasons.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Particularly Sensitive Sea Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area that needs special protection through action by IMO because of its significance for regional ecological, socio-economic or scientific reasons and because it may be vulnerable to damage by international shipping activities.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Disengagement Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area near a fairway where vessels can go to clear the way or make an about turn and possibly return to a waiting area when nautical conditions impose it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port Security Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which defence, law and treaty enforcement, and counter-terrorism activities that fall within the port and maritime domain apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coral Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where coral is protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recreation Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which recreational activities regularly take place and therefore vessel movement may be restricted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maritime Notification Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which notification is required between respective military authorities of future military exercises/activities.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Exposition of Sounding
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates the relationship of the depth of a feature to the range of depth of the surrounding depth area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Within the Range of Depth of the Surrounding Depth Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth corresponds to the depth range of the surrounding depth area; that is, the depth is not shoaler than the minimum depth of the surrounding depth area or deeper than the maximum depth of the surrounding depth area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shoaler Than the Range of Depth of the Surrounding Depth Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth is shoaler than the minimum depth of the surrounding depth area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Deeper Than the Range of Depth of the Surrounding Depth Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth is deeper than the maximum depth of the surrounding depth area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Controlled Airspace Class Designation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Air traffic services and rules of operation (e.g. instrument (IFR), and, visual (VFR), flight rules etc.) that are applicable to the controlled airspace, as defined by the governing aviation authority and in accordance with ICAO standards.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Buoy Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The principal shape and/or design of a buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Conical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has approximately the shape or the appearance of a pointed cone with the point upwards.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Can
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the shape of a cylinder, or a truncated cone that approximates to a cylinder, with a flat end uppermost.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spherical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Shaped like a sphere, which is a body the surface of which is at all points equidistant from the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pillar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure is a narrow vertical structure, pillar or lattice tower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a pole, or of a very long cylinder, floating upright.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Barrel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a barrel or cylinder floating horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Superbuoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A very large buoy designed to carry a signal light of high luminous intensity at a high elevation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Buoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specially constructed shuttle shaped buoy which is used in ice conditions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Height/Length Units
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Units of measure of waterway distances.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Metres
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The basic unit of length in the International System of Units (SI) system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Feet
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit of length equal to 12 inches, 1/6 of a fathom, or 30.480 centimetres.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Radio Station
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of radio services offered by a radio station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: circular (non-directional) marine or aero-marine radiobeacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 1:circular (non-directional) marine or aero-marine radiobeacon (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Directional Radiobeacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A special type of radiobeacon station the emissions of which are intended to provide a definite track for guidance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rotating Pattern Radiobeacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A special type of radiobeacon station emitting a beam of waves to which a uniform turning movement is given, the bearing of the station being determined by means of an ordinary listening receiver and a stop watch. Also referred to as a rotating loop radiobeacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Consol Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A type of long range position fixing beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: radio direction-finding station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 5:radio direction-finding station (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coast Radio Station Providing QTG Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radio station which is prepared to provide QTG service; that is to say, to transmit upon request from a ship a radio signal, the bearing of which can be taken by that ship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aeronautical Radiobeacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radio beacon designed for aeronautical use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Decca
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The Decca Navigator System is a high accuracy, short to medium range radio navigational aid intended for coastal and landfall navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Loran-C
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 9:Loran-C (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Differential GNSS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Differential GNSS is implemented by placing a GNSS monitor receiver at a precisely known location. Instead of computing a navigation fix, the monitor determines the range error to every GNSS satellite it can track. These ranging errors are then transmitted to local users where they are applied as corrections before computing the navigation result.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Toran
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An electronic position fixing system used mainly by aircraft.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Omega
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A long-range radio navigational aid which operates within the VLF frequency band. The system comprises eight land based stations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Syledis
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A ranging position fixing system operating at 420-450 MHz over a range of up to 400 Km.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chaika
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A low frequency electronic position fixing system using pulsed transmissions at 100 Khz.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio Telephone Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The equipment needed at one station to carry on two way voice communication by radio waves only.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Base Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An onshore AIS unit that monitors traffic in the waterways.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The right-hand channel width of a Q-Route expressed as the measurement taken from the route centreline to the channel limit when proceeding UP a Q-route (e.g. A to B to C to D).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source ID
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A unique identifier assigned to the source for reference and tracking purposes.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Rescue Station
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of aid station based on life saving equipment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rescue Station with Lifeboat
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where equipment for saving life at sea is maintained; the type of lifeboat may vary from fast, long distance boats to inflatable inshore boats.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rescue Station with Rocket
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A life saving station equipped with line-carrying rocket apparatus.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Refuge for Shipwrecked Mariners
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Shelter or protection from danger or distress at sea.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Refuge for Intertidal Area Walkers
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Shelter or protection from danger in areas exposed to extreme and sudden tides or tidal streams.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lifeboat Lying at a Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where a lifeboat is moored ready for use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aid Radio Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radio station reserved for emergency situations; might also be a public telephone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: First Aid Equipment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where first aid equipment is available.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Product
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The various substances which are transported, stored or exploited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Oil
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A thick, slippery liquid that will not dissolve in water, usually petroleum based in the context of storage tanks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A substance with particles that can move freely, usually a fuel substance in the context of storage tanks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A colourless, odourless, tasteless liquid that is a compound of hydrogen and oxygen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A general term for rock and rock fragments ranging in size from pebbles and gravel to boulders or large rock masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A hard black mineral that is burned as fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid rock or mineral from which metal is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chemicals
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any substance obtained by or used in a chemical process.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drinking Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Water that is suitable for human consumption.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Milk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A white fluid secreted by female mammals as food for their young.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bauxite
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mineral from which aluminum is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coke
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid substance obtained after gas and tar have been extracted from coal, used as a fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Iron Ingots
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An oblong lump of cast iron metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Salt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Sodium chloride obtained from mines or by the evaporation of sea water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Timber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Wood prepared for use in building or carpentry.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 16:sawdust/wood chips (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scrap Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Discarded metal suitable for being reprocessed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 18:liquefied natural gas (LNG) (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Petroleum Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A compressed gas consisting of flammable light hydrocarbons and derived from petroleum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fermented juice of grapes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cement
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A substance made of powdered lime and clay, mixed with water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Grain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A small hard seed, especially that of any cereal plant such as wheat, rice, corn, rye etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Electricity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Electric charge or current.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The solid form of water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of less than 0.002mm); stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Solid Fuel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Solid fuel: material wherein the particles firmly cohere; is hard and compact; and is burnt as a source of heat or power.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flammable Liquids And Gases
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Flammable liquids and gases: a substance which is either; in a state where molecules move freely about one another but do not fly apart; or in a condition in which it has no definite boundaries or fixed volume; but which is combustible under normal atmospheric conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ferrous Elements And Ores
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Ferrous elements and ores: unrefined and refined: a chemically inseparable substance or solid naturally occurring mineral aggregate, from which one or more valuable constituents may be recovered by treatment or a manufacturing process, and which does contain iron in its trivalent form.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Non Ferrous Elements And Ores
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Non ferrous elements and ores: unrefined and refined: A chemically inseparable substance or solid naturally occurring mineral aggregate, from which one or more valuable constituents may be recovered by treatment or a manufacturing process, and which does not contain iron in its trivalent form.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Minerals
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Substances produced by a process of in-organic nature; a substance neither animal or vegetable. Normally obtained by mining.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fertiliser
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Natural and Chemical: a substance added to the soil to increase its productivity. It may be produced by or pertaining to nature; not the work of man; or which may be formed from a substance or resulting from a reaction involving changes to atoms or molecules.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wood
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Unprocessed and Products: the substance of trees. In unprocessed form, the wood has not undergone change by a method of manufacture into products, being the manufacture of goods or commodities from wood.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rubber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Unprocessed and Products: Strong waterproof elastic material, originally made from the dried sap of a tropical tree, now usually synthetic. In unprocessed form, the rubber has not undergone change by a method of manufacture into products, being the manufacture of goods or commodities from rubber.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Items relating to the whole or most; not specialised; of broad overall character. Mixed; characterised by scope or variety; items combined or associated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Granular Or Powdery Material
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Physical matter consisting of a relatively small and hard, but usually separate particles; or in a form which is dusty or easily crumbled into tiny, loose particles.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Machinery; apparatus usually powered by electricity designed to perform a specific task. Mechanical parts; components of vehicles or machines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Construction Materials
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: That out of which anything is, or may be made; equipment or implements. Parts that may be put together.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vehicles
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A means of conveyance or transport especially a structure with wheels in or on which people or things are transported by land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aircraft
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Structure or machine for travelling in the air.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Railway
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rail or set of parallel rails on which a train, tram, or rail wagon runs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Portable Buildings
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Movable structures for giving shelter, normally prefabricated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Containers
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Boxes for cargo transport with standardized dimensions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Electronics
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Devices based on the technology of the conduction of electricity in a vacuum, gas or a semiconductor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Plastic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from plastic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Paint
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Colouring matter, especially in liquid form for imparting colour to a surface.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: refuse (also known as rubbish/garbage/trash) and waste
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 530:refuse (also known as rubbish/garbage/trash) and waste (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radioactive Material
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Relating to, caused by or exhibiting radioactivity; emission of radian elements capable of spontaneously emitting alpha, beta or sometimes gamma rays by the disintegration of the nuclei of atoms

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vertical clearance measured from the horizontal plane towards the feature overhead.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The extreme distance at which a feature can be seen or a signal detected.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Based On Fixed Marks
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A straight route (known as a recommended track, range or leading line), which comprises: a. at least two structures (usually beacons or daymarks) and/or natural features, which may carry lights and/or top-marks. The structures/features are positioned so that when observed to be in line, a vessel can follow a known bearing with safety. (Adapted from International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA Aids to Navigation Guide, 1990); or b. a single structure or natural feature, which may carry lights and/or a topmark, and a specified bearing which can be followed with safety. (S-57 Edition 3.1, Appendix A Chapter 2, Page 2.72, November 2000, as amended).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the manoeuvrability of the ferry vessel, not the various types of ferry vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Free Moving Ferry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A ferry which may have routes that vary with weather, tide and traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cable Ferry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A ferry that follows a fixed route guided by a cable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Ferry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A winter-time ferry which crosses a lead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Speed Ferry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A high speed water vessel for civilian use.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Width
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the shorter of two linear axis.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Edition Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Date of publishing for example of a publication, chart, or product.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Obstruction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of objects that impede movement.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: snag/stump
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 1:snag/stump (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wellhead
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A submarine structure projecting some distance above the seabed and capping a temporarily abandoned or suspended oil or gas well.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diffuser
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure on an outfall through which liquids are discharged. The structure will usually project above the level of the outfall and can be an obstruction to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Crib
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A permanent marine structure usually designed to support or elevate pipelines; especially a structure enclosing a screening device at the offshore end of a potable water intake pipe. The structure is commonly a heavy timber enclosure that has been sunken with rocks or other debris.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fish Haven
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Areas established by private interests, usually sport fishermen, to simulate natural reefs and wrecks that attract fish. The reefs are constructed by dumping assorted junk in areas which may be of very small extent or may stretch a considerable distance along a depth contour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Foul Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area of numerous unidentified dangers to navigation. The area serves as a warning to the mariner that all dangers are not identified individually and that navigation through the area may be hazardous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Boom
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Floating barriers, anchored to the bottom, used to deflect the path of floating ice in order to prevent the obstruction of locks, intakes, etc., and to prevent damage to bridge piers and other structures.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ground Tackle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Equipment such as anchors, concrete blocks, chains and cables, etc., used to position floating structures such as trot and mooring buoys etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boom
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A floating barrier used to protect a river or harbour mouth or to create a sheltered area for storage purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wave Energy Device
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A device to extract energy from the surface motion of ocean waves or from pressure fluctuations below the surface.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: subsurface ocean data acquisition system (ODAS)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 13:subsurface ocean data acquisition system (ODAS) (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Artificial Reef
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A man-made structure that may mimic some of the characteristics of a natural reef, intended to attract sea life.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Template
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure placed on the seafloor below a drilling rig to guide the drill.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Manifold
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large steel structure up to 20 metres in height above the seafloor, or a steel frame secured to the seafloor with piles to anchor the end of a submarine pipeline, for delivery to a production platform.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Submerged Pingo
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A hill of soil-covered ice pushed up by hydrostatic pressure in an area of permafrost that is located underwater.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Remains of Platform
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The distributed remains of a platform.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scientific Instrument
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An instrument used for scientific purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Underwater Turbine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of various machines having a rotor, usually with vanes or blades, driven by the pressure, momentum, or reactive thrust of a moving fluid, as steam, water, hot gases, or air, either occurring in the form of free jets or as a fluid passing through and entirely filling a housing around the rotor and is located underwater.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Active Submarine Volcano
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An active seabed volcano, which may be submerged or projecting above the water at the chart sounding datum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shark Net
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A submerged net placed around beaches to reduce shark attacks on swimmers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mangrove
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: One of several genera of tropical trees or shrubs which produce many prop roots and grow along low-lying coasts into shallow water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Well Protection Structure
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure, typically a dome or cube, erected over a wellhead or equipment attached to it (a tree) to lessen the danger of vessels snagging gear. (AML)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Subsea Installation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any oil or gas related installation or structure on, or projecting from, the seabed, for example a submerged platform or concrete foundations. (AML)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pipeline Obstruction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any pipeline related structure which projects above the seabed, for example a joint, T-piece, valve or sleeve, or a crossing where one pipeline is raised over another by means of a supporting structure. (AML)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: free standing conductor pipe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 504:free standing conductor pipe (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Storage Tank
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: large seabed structures, typically made of concrete, capable of storing oil or gas and usually found attached or adjacent to a rig, or marked by a single point mooring buoy. (AML)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pontoon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A floating structure, usually rectangular in shape which serves as landing, pier head, bridge support, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sundry Objects
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: miscellaneous items and objects, most of which have been lost overboard or otherwise abandoned to the sea, for example cargo containers or vehicles. (AML)

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Periodic Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The start of the active period for a seasonal object (for example a buoy).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Restriction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The official legal statute of each kind of restricted area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which anchoring is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anchoring Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which anchoring is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fishing Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which fishing is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fishing Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which fishing is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Trawling Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which trawling is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Trawling Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which trawling is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Entry Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which navigation and/or anchoring is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Entry Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which navigation is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dredging Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which dredging is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dredging Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which dredging is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diving Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which diving is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diving Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which diving is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Wake
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Mariners must adjust the speed of their vessels to reduce the wave or wash which may cause erosion or disturb moored vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Area To Be Avoided
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An IMO declared routeing measure comprising an area within defined limits in which either navigation is particularly hazardous or it is exceptionally important to avoid casualties and which should be avoided by all ships, or certain classes of ships.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Construction Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The erection of permanent or temporary fixed structures or artificial islands is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Discharging Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which discharging or dumping is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Discharging Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by an appropriate authority, within which discharging or dumping is restricted in accordance with specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 19:industrial or mineral (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drilling Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which excavating a hole on the seabed with a drill is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drilling Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by an appropriate authority, within which excavating a hole on the seabed with a drill is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which the dragging of anything along the seabed, for example bottom trawling, is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stopping Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which a vessel is prohibited from stopping.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Landing Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which landing is prohibited.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Line Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector line length specifies the displayed length of the line, in ground units, defining the limit of the sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Underlying Layer
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The position of the seabed type within the layers of the seabed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ACLANT grid
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The ACLANT (Allied Command Atlantic) submarine grid provides NATO submarine operating authorities with a common grid for the water space management of NATO submarines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Surface Danger Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which certain activities or factors of significance to surface navigation or operations apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Submarine Danger Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which submarine operations are prohibited or limited, owing to the existence of hazards to dived submarines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Testing and Evaluation Range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified zone for the provision of sonar calibration or other underwater testing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Impact area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 510:Impact area (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Live Fire Range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area used for live firing of weapons to bombard a designated area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sonar Signal Strength
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An indication of the strength of the echo of a sonic signal returned from an object.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not as good as it could be or should.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Strong
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not easily broken or destroyed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vessels Characteristics
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Characteristics of vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Length Overall
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The maximum length of the ship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Length at Waterline
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The ship's length measured at the waterline.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Breadth
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The width or beam of the vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Draught
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth of water necessary to float a vessel fully loaded.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Displacement Tonnage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the weight of the vessel, usually used for warships. (Merchant ships are usually measured based on the volume of cargo space; see tonnage). Displacement is expressed either in long tons of 2,240 pounds or metric tonnes of 1,000 kg. Since the two units are very close in size (2,240 pounds = 1,016 kg and 1,000 kg = 2,205 pounds), it is common not to distinguish between them. To preserve secrecy, nations sometimes misstate a warship's displacement.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Gross Tonnage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The entire internal cubic capacity of the ship expressed in tons of 100 cubic feet to the ton, except certain spaces with are exempted such as: peak and other tanks for water ballast, open forecastle bridge and poop, access of hatchways, certain light and air spaces, domes of skylights, condenser, anchor gear, steering gear, wheel house, galley and cabin for passengers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Net Tonnage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Obtained from the gross tonnage by deducting crew and navigating spaces and allowances for propulsion machinery.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates the source which subsequently confirmed the object

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Visitors Mooring
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A mooring set aside for the use of visiting vessels.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Conspicuous
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A feature which returns a strong radar echo.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Current Scour Dimensions
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The length, width, depth and orientation of the longest dimension of a scour that is associated with the object and that is caused by the action of currents.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Moire Effect
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A short range (up to 2km) type of directional light. Sodium lighting gives a yellow background to a screen on which a vertical black line will be seen by an observer on the centre line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Spudded Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date on which a new well is spudded, meaning to start drilling a new borehole.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The total vertical length of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Coverage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicator as to area of data coverage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coverage Available
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous coverage of spatial objects is available within this area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Coverage Available
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area containing no spatial objects.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Communication Channel
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A channel number assigned to a specific radio frequency, frequencies or frequency band.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the fixed horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Clearance Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The physical horizontal clearance distance between two points on a feature, such as a bridge span, dock, gate, lock or tunnel.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Beacon Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Describes the characteristic geometric form of the beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 1:stake, pole, perch, post (missing definition)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Withy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tree without roots stuck or spoiled into the bottom of the sea to serve as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid structure of the order of 10 metres in height used as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lattice Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure consisting of strips of metal or wood crossed or interlaced to form a structure to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pile Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A long heavy timber(s) or section(s) of steel, wood, concrete, etc., forced into the seabed to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised as a landmark or to designate a point of importance in surveying.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyant Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall spar-like beacon fitted with a permanently submerged buoyancy chamber, the lower end of the body is secured to seabed sinker either by a flexible joint or by a cable under tension.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Variable Factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The factor to be applied to the variable component of an uncertainty equation so as to provide the best estimate of the variable horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Dumping Ground
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an area based on the type of waste being disposed of.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chemical Waste Dumping Ground
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area at sea where chemical waste is dumped.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nuclear Waste Dumping Ground
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area at sea where nuclear waste is dumped.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Explosives Dumping Ground

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Heavy Lift

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ballast

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dry Bulk Cargo

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquid Bulk Cargo

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reefer Container Cargo

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Interrupted Ultra Quick-Flashing

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IUCN Category II

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IUCN Category III

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IUCN Category IV

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IUCN Category V
